{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":611,"text":"For me they normally happen,\nthese career crises,"},{"time":3008,"text":"often, actually, on a Sunday evening,"},{"time":5579,"text":"just as the sun is starting to set,"},{"time":7476,"text":"and the gap between my hopes for myself\nand the reality of my life"},{"time":12158,"text":"starts to diverge so painfully"},{"time":14000,"text":"that I normally end up\nweeping into a pillow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"I'm mentioning all this --"},{"time":18529,"text":"I'm mentioning all this because I think\nthis is not merely a personal problem;"},{"time":22236,"text":"you may think I'm wrong in this,"},{"time":23796,"text":"but I think we live in an age\nwhen our lives are regularly punctuated"},{"time":27403,"text":"by career crises, by moments\nwhen what we thought we knew --"},{"time":30569,"text":"about our lives, about our careers --"},{"time":32403,"text":"comes into contact\nwith a threatening sort of reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35856,"text":"It's perhaps easier now than ever before\nto make a good living."},{"time":39633,"text":"It's perhaps harder than ever before"},{"time":42000,"text":"to stay calm, to be free\nof career anxiety."},{"time":45000,"text":"I want to look now, if I may,\nat some of the reasons"},{"time":48413,"text":"why we might be feeling\nanxiety about our careers."},{"time":52000,"text":"Why we might be victims\nof these career crises,"},{"time":54263,"text":"as we're weeping softly into our pillows."},{"time":58233,"text":"One of the reasons\nwhy we might be suffering"},{"time":61000,"text":"is that we are surrounded by snobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63582,"text":"In a way, I've got some bad news,"},{"time":66000,"text":"particularly to anybody\nwho's come to Oxford from abroad."},{"time":68786,"text":"There's a real problem with snobbery,"},{"time":70588,"text":"because sometimes people\nfrom outside the U.K."},{"time":72778,"text":"imagine that snobbery\nis a distinctively U.K. phenomenon,"},{"time":75509,"text":"fixated on country houses and titles."},{"time":78000,"text":"The bad news is that's not true."},{"time":79688,"text":"Snobbery is a global phenomenon;\nwe are a global organization,"},{"time":82688,"text":"this is a global phenomenon."},{"time":84069,"text":"What is a snob?"},{"time":85728,"text":"A snob is anybody who takes\na small part of you,"},{"time":89061,"text":"and uses that to come\nto a complete vision of who you are."},{"time":92450,"text":"That is snobbery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"The dominant kind of snobbery\nthat exists nowadays is job snobbery."},{"time":98349,"text":"You encounter it within minutes\nat a party, when you get asked"},{"time":101620,"text":"that famous iconic question\nof the early 21st century,"},{"time":104811,"text":"\"What do you do?\""},{"time":106008,"text":"According to how you answer that question,"},{"time":108033,"text":"people are either incredibly\ndelighted to see you,"},{"time":110391,"text":"or look at their watch\nand make their excuses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112597,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113637,"text":"Now, the opposite of a snob\nis your mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"Not necessarily your mother,\nor indeed mine,"},{"time":121001,"text":"but, as it were, the ideal mother,"},{"time":122660,"text":"somebody who doesn't care\nabout your achievements."},{"time":125032,"text":"Unfortunately, most people\nare not our mothers."},{"time":127254,"text":"Most people make a strict correlation\nbetween how much time,"},{"time":130096,"text":"and if you like, love --"},{"time":131513,"text":"not romantic love,\nthough that may be something --"},{"time":134000,"text":"but love in general, respect --\nthey are willing to accord us,"},{"time":137319,"text":"that will be strictly defined\nby our position in the social hierarchy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"And that's a lot of the reason\nwhy we care so much about our careers"},{"time":144263,"text":"and indeed start caring\nso much about material goods."},{"time":148000,"text":"You know, we're often told\nthat we live in very materialistic times,"},{"time":151263,"text":"that we're all greedy people."},{"time":153000,"text":"I don't think we are\nparticularly materialistic."},{"time":155310,"text":"I think we live in a society which has\nsimply pegged certain emotional rewards"},{"time":159762,"text":"to the acquisition of material goods."},{"time":161998,"text":"It's not the material goods we want;\nit's the rewards we want."},{"time":164952,"text":"It's a new way of looking at luxury goods."},{"time":166984,"text":"The next time you see somebody\ndriving a Ferrari, don't think,"},{"time":169969,"text":"\"This is somebody who's greedy.\""},{"time":171817,"text":"Think, \"This is somebody who is incredibly\nvulnerable and in need of love.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":175559,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Feel sympathy, rather than contempt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181427,"text":"There are other reasons --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182959,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"There are other reasons why it's perhaps\nharder now to feel calm than ever before."},{"time":187946,"text":"One of these, and it's paradoxical,"},{"time":189646,"text":"because it's linked to something\nthat's rather nice,"},{"time":192180,"text":"is the hope we all have for our careers."},{"time":194250,"text":"Never before have\nexpectations been so high"},{"time":196372,"text":"about what human beings can\nachieve with their lifespan."},{"time":199119,"text":"We're told, from many sources,\nthat anyone can achieve anything."},{"time":202172,"text":"We've done away with the caste system,"},{"time":204079,"text":"we are now in a system where anyone\ncan rise to any position they please."},{"time":207794,"text":"And it's a beautiful idea."},{"time":210000,"text":"Along with that is a kind\nof spirit of equality;"},{"time":212477,"text":"we're all basically equal."},{"time":213858,"text":"There are no strictly defined hierarchies."},{"time":218000,"text":"There is one really big problem with this,"},{"time":220486,"text":"and that problem is envy."},{"time":222519,"text":"Envy, it's a real taboo to mention envy,"},{"time":224806,"text":"but if there's one dominant emotion\nin modern society, that is envy."},{"time":228310,"text":"And it's linked to the spirit of equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231001,"text":"Let me explain."},{"time":232176,"text":"I think it would be very unusual\nfor anyone here, or anyone watching,"},{"time":235461,"text":"to be envious of the Queen of England."},{"time":237357,"text":"Even though she is much richer\nthan any of you are,"},{"time":240618,"text":"and she's got a very large house,"},{"time":242904,"text":"the reason why we don't envy her\nis because she's too weird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246586,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":247618,"text":"She's simply too strange."},{"time":248999,"text":"We can't relate to her,\nshe speaks in a funny way,"},{"time":251404,"text":"she comes from an odd place."},{"time":252801,"text":"So we can't relate to her,"},{"time":254198,"text":"and when you can't relate\nto somebody, you don't envy them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257120,"text":"The closer two people are --\nin age, in background,"},{"time":260000,"text":"in the process of identification --\nthe more there's a danger of envy,"},{"time":263342,"text":"which is incidentally why none of you\nshould ever go to a school reunion,"},{"time":266841,"text":"because there is no stronger reference\npoint than people one was at school with."},{"time":270964,"text":"The problem of modern society is\nit turns the whole world into a school."},{"time":274526,"text":"Everybody's wearing jeans,\neverybody's the same."},{"time":276820,"text":"And yet, they're not."},{"time":277999,"text":"So there's a spirit of equality\ncombined with deep inequality,"},{"time":281000,"text":"which can make for\na very stressful situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283715,"text":"It's probably as unlikely\nthat you would nowadays"},{"time":286064,"text":"become as rich and famous as Bill Gates,"},{"time":288000,"text":"as it was unlikely in the 17th century"},{"time":290000,"text":"that you would accede to the ranks\nof the French aristocracy."},{"time":293266,"text":"But the point is,\nit doesn't feel that way."},{"time":295338,"text":"It's made to feel, by magazines\nand other media outlets,"},{"time":298428,"text":"that if you've got energy, a few bright\nideas about technology, a garage --"},{"time":302308,"text":"you, too, could start a major thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304763,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306142,"text":"The consequences of this problem\nmake themselves felt in bookshops."},{"time":309405,"text":"When you go to a large bookshop\nand look at the self-help sections,"},{"time":312620,"text":"as I sometimes do --"},{"time":313824,"text":"if you analyze self-help books\nproduced in the world today,"},{"time":316934,"text":"there are basically two kinds."},{"time":318405,"text":"The first kind tells you, \"You can do it!\nYou can make it! Anything's possible!\""},{"time":322215,"text":"The other kind tells you how to cope with\nwhat we politely call \"low self-esteem,\""},{"time":326835,"text":"or impolitely call,\n\"feeling very bad about yourself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":329486,"text":"There's a real correlation"},{"time":331000,"text":"between a society that tells people\nthat they can do anything,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and the existence of low self-esteem."},{"time":337000,"text":"So that's another way in which something\nquite positive can have a nasty kickback."},{"time":341000,"text":"There is another reason why\nwe might be feeling more anxious --"},{"time":344349,"text":"about our careers, about our status\nin the world today, than ever before."},{"time":348000,"text":"And it's, again, linked to something nice."},{"time":350072,"text":"And that nice thing is called meritocracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352794,"text":"Everybody, all politicians\non Left and Right,"},{"time":355120,"text":"agree that meritocracy is a great thing,"},{"time":357361,"text":"and we should all be trying to make\nour societies really, really meritocratic."},{"time":361531,"text":"In other words --\nwhat is a meritocratic society?"},{"time":364874,"text":"A meritocratic society is one in which,\nif you've got talent and energy and skill,"},{"time":369024,"text":"you will get to the top,\nnothing should hold you back."},{"time":371620,"text":"It's a beautiful idea."},{"time":372806,"text":"The problem is, if you\nreally believe in a society"},{"time":376154,"text":"where those who merit to get\nto the top, get to the top,"},{"time":378846,"text":"you'll also, by implication,\nand in a far more nasty way,"},{"time":381875,"text":"believe in a society where those\nwho deserve to get to the bottom"},{"time":385596,"text":"also get to the bottom and stay there."},{"time":387843,"text":"In other words, your position in life\ncomes to seem not accidental,"},{"time":391215,"text":"but merited and deserved."},{"time":393000,"text":"And that makes failure\nseem much more crushing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"You know, in the Middle Ages, in England,"},{"time":398402,"text":"when you met a very poor person,"},{"time":400298,"text":"that person would be described\nas an \"unfortunate\" --"},{"time":403186,"text":"literally, somebody who had not\nbeen blessed by fortune, an unfortunate."},{"time":407000,"text":"Nowadays, particularly\nin the United States,"},{"time":409120,"text":"if you meet someone\nat the bottom of society,"},{"time":411287,"text":"they may unkindly be\ndescribed as a \"loser.\""},{"time":414000,"text":"There's a real difference\nbetween an unfortunate and a loser,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and that shows 400 years\nof evolution in society"},{"time":420000,"text":"and our belief in who\nis responsible for our lives."},{"time":423121,"text":"It's no longer the gods, it's us.\nWe're in the driving seat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"That's exhilarating if you're doing well,"},{"time":428000,"text":"and very crushing if you're not."},{"time":429876,"text":"It leads, in the worst cases --"},{"time":431442,"text":"in the analysis of a sociologist\nlike Emil Durkheim --"},{"time":434433,"text":"it leads to increased rates of suicide."},{"time":436764,"text":"There are more suicides\nin developed, individualistic countries"},{"time":440000,"text":"than in any other part of the world."},{"time":441765,"text":"And some of the reason for that"},{"time":443363,"text":"is that people take what happens to them\nextremely personally --"},{"time":446456,"text":"they own their success,\nbut they also own their failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449999,"text":"Is there any relief\nfrom some of these pressures"},{"time":452310,"text":"that I've been outlining?"},{"time":453671,"text":"I think there is."},{"time":454854,"text":"I just want to turn to a few of them."},{"time":456644,"text":"Let's take meritocracy."},{"time":458000,"text":"This idea that everybody deserves\nto get where they get to,"},{"time":461000,"text":"I think it's a crazy idea,\ncompletely crazy."},{"time":463832,"text":"I will support any politician\nof Left and Right,"},{"time":466108,"text":"with any halfway-decent meritocratic idea;"},{"time":468426,"text":"I am a meritocrat in that sense."},{"time":470000,"text":"But I think it's insane to believe"},{"time":471696,"text":"that we will ever make a society\nthat is genuinely meritocratic;"},{"time":475177,"text":"it's an impossible dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476435,"text":"The idea that we will make a society\nwhere literally everybody is graded,"},{"time":479920,"text":"the good at the top, bad at the bottom,"},{"time":481840,"text":"exactly done as it\nshould be, is impossible."},{"time":484000,"text":"There are simply too many random factors:"},{"time":486000,"text":"accidents, accidents of birth,"},{"time":488000,"text":"accidents of things dropping\non people's heads, illnesses, etc."},{"time":491024,"text":"We will never get to grade them,"},{"time":493000,"text":"never get to grade people as they should."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"I'm drawn to a lovely quote\nby St. Augustine in \"The City of God,\""},{"time":498167,"text":"where he says, \"It's a sin\nto judge any man by his post.\""},{"time":502604,"text":"In modern English that would mean"},{"time":504270,"text":"it's a sin to come to any view\nof who you should talk to,"},{"time":507018,"text":"dependent on their business card."},{"time":508625,"text":"It's not the post that should count."},{"time":510400,"text":"According to St. Augustine, only God\ncan really put everybody in their place;"},{"time":514204,"text":"he's going to do that\non the Day of Judgment,"},{"time":516363,"text":"with angels and trumpets,\nand the skies will open."},{"time":518769,"text":"Insane idea, if you're\na secularist person, like me."},{"time":521300,"text":"But something very valuable\nin that idea, nevertheless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523944,"text":"In other words, hold your horses\nwhen you're coming to judge people."},{"time":527300,"text":"You don't necessarily know\nwhat someone's true value is."},{"time":530000,"text":"That is an unknown part of them,"},{"time":532000,"text":"and we shouldn't behave\nas though it is known."},{"time":535219,"text":"There is another source of solace\nand comfort for all this."},{"time":538044,"text":"When we think about failing in life,\nwhen we think about failure,"},{"time":541193,"text":"one of the reasons why we fear failing"},{"time":543059,"text":"is not just a loss of income,\na loss of status."},{"time":545358,"text":"What we fear is the judgment\nand ridicule of others."},{"time":548125,"text":"And it exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549302,"text":"The number one organ of ridicule,\nnowadays, is the newspaper."},{"time":552882,"text":"If you open the newspaper\nany day of the week,"},{"time":555095,"text":"it's full of people\nwho've messed up their lives."},{"time":557435,"text":"They've slept with the wrong person,\ntaken the wrong substance,"},{"time":560452,"text":"passed the wrong piece of legislation --"},{"time":562498,"text":"whatever it is, and then\nare fit for ridicule."},{"time":564690,"text":"In other words, they have failed.\nAnd they are described as \"losers.\""},{"time":567999,"text":"Now, is there any alternative to this?"},{"time":569851,"text":"I think the Western tradition shows us one\nglorious alternative, which is tragedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574471,"text":"Tragic art, as it developed\nin the theaters of ancient Greece,"},{"time":577717,"text":"in the fifth century B.C.,\nwas essentially an art form"},{"time":580511,"text":"devoted to tracing how people fail,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and also according them\na level of sympathy,"},{"time":587407,"text":"which ordinary life would not\nnecessarily accord them."},{"time":590707,"text":"A few years ago,\nI was thinking about this,"},{"time":592771,"text":"and I went to \"The Sunday Sport,\""},{"time":594390,"text":"a tabloid newspaper I don't\nrecommend you start reading"},{"time":597024,"text":"if you're not familiar with it already."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598945,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599977,"text":"And I went to talk to them"},{"time":601243,"text":"about certain of the great\ntragedies of Western art."},{"time":604008,"text":"I wanted to see how they would seize\nthe bare bones of certain stories,"},{"time":607617,"text":"if they came in as a news item\nat the news desk on a Saturday afternoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611601,"text":"I mentioned Othello; they'd not\nheard of it but were fascinated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614749,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615781,"text":"I asked them to write\na headline for the story."},{"time":618107,"text":"They came up with \"Love-Crazed\nImmigrant Kills Senator's Daughter.\""},{"time":621570,"text":"Splashed across the headline."},{"time":623000,"text":"I gave them the plotline of Madame Bovary."},{"time":625024,"text":"Again, a book they were\nenchanted to discover."},{"time":627239,"text":"And they wrote \"Shopaholic Adulteress\nSwallows Arsenic After Credit Fraud.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":632000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633040,"text":"And then my favorite --"},{"time":634247,"text":"they really do have a kind of genius\nof their own, these guys --"},{"time":637350,"text":"my favorite is Sophocles'\nOedipus the King:"},{"time":639468,"text":"\"Sex With Mum Was Blinding.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"In a way, if you like, at one end\nof the spectrum of sympathy,"},{"time":650000,"text":"you've got the tabloid newspaper."},{"time":651817,"text":"At the other end of the spectrum,\nyou've got tragedy and tragic art."},{"time":655032,"text":"And I suppose I'm arguing\nthat we should learn a little bit"},{"time":657830,"text":"about what's happening in tragic art."},{"time":659640,"text":"It would be insane to call Hamlet a loser."},{"time":662362,"text":"He is not a loser, though he has lost."},{"time":664697,"text":"And I think that is the message\nof tragedy to us,"},{"time":667358,"text":"and why it's so very,\nvery important, I think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"The other thing about modern society\nand why it causes this anxiety,"},{"time":674000,"text":"is that we have nothing at its center\nthat is non-human."},{"time":677000,"text":"We are the first society\nto be living in a world"},{"time":679612,"text":"where we don't worship\nanything other than ourselves."},{"time":682128,"text":"We think very highly of ourselves,\nand so we should;"},{"time":684597,"text":"we've put people on the Moon,\ndone all sorts of extraordinary things."},{"time":687914,"text":"And so we tend to worship ourselves.\nOur heroes are human heroes."},{"time":691231,"text":"That's a very new situation."},{"time":692818,"text":"Most other societies have had,\nright at their center,"},{"time":695349,"text":"the worship of something transcendent:\na god, a spirit, a natural force,"},{"time":698794,"text":"the universe, whatever it is --\nsomething else that is being worshiped."},{"time":702168,"text":"We've slightly lost\nthe habit of doing that,"},{"time":704264,"text":"which is, I think, why we're\nparticularly drawn to nature."},{"time":707056,"text":"Not for the sake of our health,\nthough it's often presented that way,"},{"time":710336,"text":"but because it's an escape\nfrom the human anthill."},{"time":713000,"text":"It's an escape from our own competition,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and our own dramas."},{"time":717000,"text":"And that's why we enjoy looking\nat glaciers and oceans,"},{"time":719644,"text":"and contemplating the Earth\nfrom outside its perimeters, etc."},{"time":723619,"text":"We like to feel in contact\nwith something that is non-human,"},{"time":727222,"text":"and that is so deeply important to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"What I think I've been talking\nabout really is success and failure."},{"time":734215,"text":"And one of the interesting\nthings about success"},{"time":736668,"text":"is that we think we know what it means."},{"time":738676,"text":"If I said that there's somebody\nbehind the screen who's very successful,"},{"time":742097,"text":"certain ideas would\nimmediately come to mind."},{"time":744498,"text":"You'd think that person\nmight have made a lot of money,"},{"time":747172,"text":"achieved renown in some field."},{"time":749104,"text":"My own theory of success --"},{"time":750457,"text":"I'm somebody who's\nvery interested in success,"},{"time":752640,"text":"I really want to be successful,"},{"time":754145,"text":"always thinking,\nhow can I be more successful?"},{"time":756351,"text":"But as I get older, I'm also very nuanced\nabout what that word \"success\" might mean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760705,"text":"Here's an insight\nthat I've had about success:"},{"time":762943,"text":"You can't be successful at everything."},{"time":764848,"text":"We hear a lot of talk\nabout work-life balance."},{"time":767135,"text":"Nonsense."},{"time":768310,"text":"You can't have it all. You can't."},{"time":770000,"text":"So any vision of success\nhas to admit what it's losing out on,"},{"time":774499,"text":"where the element of loss is."},{"time":776200,"text":"And I think any wise life will accept,"},{"time":778748,"text":"as I say, that there is going to be\nan element where we're not succeeding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782548,"text":"And the thing about a successful life\nis that a lot of the time,"},{"time":785580,"text":"our ideas of what it would mean\nto live successfully are not our own."},{"time":789494,"text":"They're sucked in from other people;"},{"time":791233,"text":"chiefly, if you're a man, your father,\nand if you're a woman, your mother."},{"time":794861,"text":"Psychoanalysis has been drumming home\nthis message for about 80 years."},{"time":798250,"text":"No one's quite listening hard enough,\nbut I very much believe it's true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801781,"text":"And we also suck in messages\nfrom everything from the television,"},{"time":804923,"text":"to advertising, to marketing, etc."},{"time":806733,"text":"These are hugely powerful forces"},{"time":809000,"text":"that define what we want\nand how we view ourselves."},{"time":813000,"text":"When we're told that banking\nis a very respectable profession,"},{"time":816000,"text":"a lot of us want to go into banking."},{"time":818000,"text":"When banking is no longer so respectable,\nwe lose interest in banking."},{"time":821358,"text":"We are highly open to suggestion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824440,"text":"So what I want to argue for\nis not that we should give up"},{"time":827361,"text":"on our ideas of success,"},{"time":829000,"text":"but we should make sure\nthat they are our own."},{"time":831215,"text":"We should focus in on our ideas,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and make sure that we own them;"},{"time":835755,"text":"that we are truly the authors\nof our own ambitions."},{"time":838200,"text":"Because it's bad enough\nnot getting what you want,"},{"time":841025,"text":"but it's even worse to have\nan idea of what it is you want,"},{"time":844136,"text":"and find out, at the end of the journey,"},{"time":846200,"text":"that it isn't, in fact,\nwhat you wanted all along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849388,"text":"So, I'm going to end it there."},{"time":851000,"text":"But what I really want to stress is:\nby all means, success, yes."},{"time":856000,"text":"But let's accept the strangeness\nof some of our ideas."},{"time":858596,"text":"Let's probe away\nat our notions of success."},{"time":861365,"text":"Let's make sure our ideas of success\nare truly our own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":882698,"text":"Chris Anderson: That was fascinating."},{"time":884539,"text":"But how do you reconcile this idea"},{"time":890000,"text":"of it being bad to think\nof someone as a \"loser,\""},{"time":892794,"text":"with the idea that a lot of people like,\nof seizing control of your life,"},{"time":897656,"text":"and that a society that encourages that,"},{"time":900585,"text":"perhaps has to have\nsome winners and losers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"Alain De Botton: Yes, I think\nit's merely the randomness"},{"time":905675,"text":"of the winning and losing process\nthat I want to stress,"},{"time":908365,"text":"because the emphasis nowadays is so much\non the justice of everything,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and politicians always talk about justice."},{"time":914025,"text":"Now I'm a firm believer in justice,\nI just think that it's impossible."},{"time":917457,"text":"So we should do everything\nwe can to pursue it,"},{"time":921084,"text":"but we should always remember\nthat whoever is facing us,"},{"time":924544,"text":"whatever has happened in their lives,"},{"time":926711,"text":"there will be a strong\nelement of the haphazard."},{"time":929000,"text":"That's what I'm trying to leave room for;"},{"time":931240,"text":"otherwise, it can get\nquite claustrophobic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933330,"text":"CA: I mean, do you believe\nthat you can combine"},{"time":935579,"text":"your kind of kinder,\ngentler philosophy of work"},{"time":937888,"text":"with a successful economy?"},{"time":941000,"text":"Or do you think that you can't,"},{"time":942806,"text":"but it doesn't matter that much that we're\nputting too much emphasis on that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":946504,"text":"AB: The nightmare thought"},{"time":948000,"text":"is that frightening people\nis the best way to get work out of them,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and that somehow\nthe crueler the environment,"},{"time":955436,"text":"the more people will rise\nto the challenge."},{"time":957825,"text":"You want to think, who would you like\nas your ideal dad?"},{"time":960794,"text":"And your ideal dad is somebody\nwho is tough but gentle."},{"time":964000,"text":"And it's a very hard line to make."},{"time":966237,"text":"We need fathers, as it were,\nthe exemplary father figures in society,"},{"time":970000,"text":"avoiding the two extremes,"},{"time":972447,"text":"which is the authoritarian\ndisciplinarian on the one hand,"},{"time":976000,"text":"and on the other,\nthe lax, no-rules option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980825,"text":"CA: Alain De Botton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982222,"text":"AB: Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984001,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}